<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-05-19T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-19T14:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2331/5–947: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-05-19T15:00:00-04:00">May 19,
                                    1947—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>247. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s 346 May 9. In view stock
                            position Peru, Dept <gloss target="#t_Agri1">Agri</gloss> has told
                            Peruvians they are now permitted buy 10,000 tons flour for as early
                            shipment as can be arranged. Peruvian <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> says flour acceptable. Most other countries taking a
                            far larger percent of imports in form of flour than is Peru.</p>
                        <p>US July export program just announced includes 8,500 tons wheat for
                            Peru.</p>
                        <p>It is hoped that these emergency allocations will improve Peru’s
                            bargaining position in its current negotiations with Argentina.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>